Given an <i>n</i>-node planar graph with nonnegative edge-lengths, our algorithm takes <i>O</i>(<i>n</i> log <i>n</i>) time to construct a data structure that supports queries of the following form in <i>O</i>(log <i>n</i>) time: given a destination node <i>t</i> on the boundary of the infinite face, and given a start node <i>s</i> anywhere, find the <i>s</i>-to-<i>t</i> distance.